description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, and highly motivated Band 5 Community Staff Nurse post, to join the Burton and surrounding areas Community Nursing Team. We are an innovative service covering GP practices in the East staffs area. As a Community Staff Nurse you will deliver a high quality service to patients in their own homes, residential settings and clinics, working closely with the GP’s and multi-disciplinary teams addressing a range of care issues across the spectrum of health conditions, and preventing avoidable hospital admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work independently in the community setting, participating in the ongoing assessment, planning, implementation and evaluation of programs of care, adhering to policies and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a qualified nurse with current NMC registration, hold a full driving license and will be required to work flexibly on a rota system across a 7 days a week, including bank holidays. You should have excellent communication and interpersonal skills and the ability to organise and prioritise your workload without direct supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Please contact Christine Atton, Operational TeamLead on 07971904899 or email Christine.atton@mpft.nhs.uk for further information.&lt;/p&gt;
